@page "/"

<PageTitle>Batby Education</PageTitle>

<h1>Batby Education</h1>
<p class="lead">Tutoring booking and accounting system</p>

<hr />

<h3>Getting Started</h3>

<div class="row g-4 mt-2">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">1. Set Up Tutors</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Register your tutors with their subjects and hourly rates, then configure their weekly availability slots.</p>
                <a href="/tutors" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">Go to Tutors</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">2. Register Students</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Add students with guardian details, optional hourly rate, and default booking preferences (tutor, subject, day, timeslot).</p>
                <a href="/students" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">Go to Students</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">3. Book Sessions</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Select a student (defaults auto-fill), pick a date, choose an available slot, and book. Override the rate if needed.</p>
                <a href="/sessions/book" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">Book a Session</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">4. Record Attendance</h5>
                <p class="card-text">After each session, mark it as completed (with actual duration) or as a no-show. View upcoming sessions in the calendar.</p>
                <a href="/sessions" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">View Sessions</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">5. Generate Invoices</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Select a student and billing period. The system calculates amounts using the rate priority chain and creates a downloadable PDF invoice.</p>
                <a href="/invoices" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">Go to Invoices</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">6. Record Payments</h5>
                <p class="card-text">Record cash or bank transfer payments against invoices. Overpayments are automatically credited to the student's account.</p>
                <a href="/payments" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">Record Payment</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr class="mt-4" />

<h3>Key Concepts</h3>

<div class="row mt-3">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h6>Rate Priority Chain</h6>
        <p class="small text-muted">When calculating invoice amounts, the system uses: <strong>Session Override</strong> &gt; <strong>Student Rate</strong> &gt; <strong>Tutor Rate</strong></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h6>Availability Slots</h6>
        <p class="small text-muted">Configure time slots per day for each tutor. When booking, you'll see available slots to click — already-booked ones are greyed out.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h6>Late Cancellations</h6>
        <p class="small text-muted">Sessions cancelled within 24 hours of the start time (or marked as no-show) are billed at the configured late cancellation fee.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row mt-2">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h6>Default Preferences</h6>
        <p class="small text-muted">Set a default tutor, subject, day, and timeslot per student. These pre-fill the booking form for quick repeat bookings.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h6>Separate Ledgers</h6>
        <p class="small text-muted">Cash and bank transfer payments are tracked in separate ledgers for independent reconciliation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <h6>Tax Year Reports</h6>
        <p class="small text-muted">Financial summaries aligned to the UK tax year (6 April – 5 April) with monthly breakdowns.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<hr class="mt-3" />

<p class="text-muted small mt-3">
    <strong>Quick links:</strong>
    <a href="/calendar">Calendar</a> ·
    <a href="/reports">Reports</a> ·
    <a href="/reports/balances">Outstanding Balances</a> ·
    <a href="/reports/tax-year">Tax Year Summary</a>
</p>
